18/02/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu said Thursday (17 February) he is convinced the country needs early general elections, either in May-June or October-November.
Prime Minister Calin Popescu Tariceanu favours early elections as well, but not before 2007.
Also Thursday, authorities re-approved the Pre-Accession Economic Programme.
The European Commission had asked for reauthorisation because of the change in government following Romania's elections.
European Commissioner for Enlargement Olli Rehn plans to visit Bucharest next month to attend a meeting of the executive committee for EU integration.
(Rompres, Nine o'clock - 17/02/05)
